    <tags>react, frontend, fluent-ui, dataverse</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Source-specific picker; queries `sprk_document` related to a parent (e.g., Matter) and resolves driveItemId for canonical attachment. STANDARD covers it; no new patterns.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <fr-refs>FR-07</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build `RelatedRecordAttachmentSource.tsx` at `subcomponents/sources/RelatedRecordAttachmentSource.tsx`. Lets the user pick from documents related to the email's host record (e.g., on a Matter's email send, pick from that matter's `sprk_document` records).

    Behavior:
    - Receives `relatedRecord: { entityName: string; recordId: string }` from props (engine forwards from host)
    - Queries Dataverse for `sprk_document` records where `_sprk_parent_value = relatedRecord.recordId` (parent lookup matches that entity)
    - Renders a Dialog with a Fluent `<List>` or `<DataGrid>` of matching documents (name, type, size)
    - On selection, resolves each `sprk_document` GUID → its `driveItemId` (`sprk_document.sprk_driveitemid` field per Dataverse schema)
    - Produces `IAttachment[]` with `source='related'`, `driveItemId: <resolved>`, `name`, `sizeBytes`, `mimeType`

    Use `Xrm.WebApi.retrieveMultipleRecords` in Code Page context (per DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md — host-context API is preferred for direct Dataverse reads). In wizard contexts (no Xrm), fall back to BFF via `authenticatedFetch`.

    Per CLAUDE.md Empirical Finding: Spaarke's `sprk_document` records have both a Dataverse GUID and a `sprk_driveitemid` field — the SPE driveItem ID. The canonical attachment id is the driveItem ID, NOT the sprk_document GUID. This is the latent bug fix from FR-17 / DocumentEmailWizard line 494.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer with Dataverse `Xrm.WebApi` + BFF fallback experience. Familiar with `sprk_document` schema (`sprk_driveitemid` field present per R1+R2 work).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `RelatedRecordAttachmentSource.tsx` compiles + lint-clean. Opens a dialog listing parent's `sprk_document` records; selecting them produces `IAttachment[]` with `driveItemId` correctly populated (NOT the document GUID — the SPE driveItem ID from `sprk_document.sprk_driveitemid`).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-07 + FR-17 + CLAUDE.md Empirical Finding #5: latent bug at DocumentEmailWizard:494 was sending `sprk_document` GUIDs instead of driveItem IDs. This component (R3) fixes that class of bug by hard-coding the resolution: pick a sprk_document → read its `sprk_driveitemid` field → use THAT as the canonical attachment reference.

      `Xrm.WebApi.retrieveMultipleRecords` is the right tool for Code Page direct-Dataverse reads per `docs/standards/DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md`. For wizard contexts inside shared lib, the BFF fallback uses an existing endpoint or the typed `documentApi.ts` if available — audit at task start.
    </background>
