  <steps>
    <step order="1">Confirm `sprk_document.sprk_driveitemid` schema field present (grep existing code or read docs/data-model/sprk_document.md if exists).</step>
    <step order="2">Audit existing Dataverse-query helpers (`documentApi.ts` or similar) for reuse.</step>
    <step order="3">Author `RelatedRecordAttachmentSource.tsx`:
      - Props: `{ relatedRecord: { entityName: string; recordId: string }; onAdd: (attachments: IAttachment[]) =&gt; void; authenticatedFetch: typeof fetch; disabled?: boolean }`
      - Detect host: `typeof Xrm !== 'undefined' &amp;&amp; Xrm.WebApi` — use `Xrm.WebApi.retrieveMultipleRecords('sprk_document', $filter: \`_sprk_parent_value eq ${recordId}\`, $select: \`sprk_documentid,sprk_name,sprk_driveitemid,sprk_mimetype,sprk_sizebytes\`)`
      - Otherwise: BFF fallback via `authenticatedFetch` to the document-list endpoint (audit for existing API)
      - Render Dialog with Fluent `&lt;DataGrid&gt;` listing returned docs
      - On selection: map docs → `IAttachment[]` with `driveItemId: doc.sprk_driveitemid` (NOT `doc.sprk_documentid` — that's the latent bug)
      - Filter out any doc whose `sprk_driveitemid` is null/empty (cannot attach without driveItem)</step>
    <step order="4">Wire into AttachmentList — when `attachmentSources` includes `{ kind: 'related' }`, render this picker; `relatedRecord` comes from engine's `associations` or a dedicated prop.</step>
    <step order="5">Update `EmailComposer/index.ts` — export `RelatedRecordAttachmentSource`.</step>
    <step order="6">Smoke test: on a Matter Code Page, open picker, pick a known document, verify `driveItemId` field populated (NOT GUID).</step>
    <step order="7">Run `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 017 ✅.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol.</step>
  </steps>

